LiMAx PK/PD Model (Pharmacokinetics/Pharmacodynamics)¶

PKPD model for clearance of methacetin by the human body.

Evaluation of model performance via time courses for methacetin, paracetamol, DOB (LiMAx).

Setup¶

In [1]:
# setting up the environment for plotting & importing tellurium for SBML simulations
%matplotlib inline
from __future__ import print_function, division
import roadrunner
import matplotlib
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import pylimax

# global settings for plots
matplotlib.style.use('classic')
plt.rcParams.update({
        'axes.labelsize': 'large', 
        'axes.labelweight': 'bold',
        'axes.titlesize': 'small',
        'axes.titleweight': 'bold',
        'legend.fontsize': 'small',
        'xtick.labelsize': 'large',
        'ytick.labelsize': 'large',
        'figure.facecolor': '1.00'
    })

substances = ["metc13", "apap", "co2c13", "apap_glu", "apap_sul", "apap_cys"]
titles = ["C13-methacetin", "paracetamol", "C13-CO2", "apap_gluc", "apap_sul", "apap_cys"]
doses_keys = ['PODOSE_{}'.format(key) for key in substances] + ['IVDOSE_{}'.format(key) for key in substances] 

def resetAll(r):
    """ Reset all model variables to CURRENT init(X) values.

    This resets all variables, S1, S2 etc to the CURRENT init(X) values. It also resets all
    parameters back to the values they had when the model was first loaded.
    """
    r.reset(roadrunner.SelectionRecord.TIME |
               roadrunner.SelectionRecord.RATE |
               roadrunner.SelectionRecord.FLOATING |
               roadrunner.SelectionRecord.GLOBAL_PARAMETER)

def print_doses(r, name=None):
    """ Prints the complete dose information of the model. """
    if name:
        print('***', name, '***')
    for key in doses_keys:
        print('{}\t{}'.format(key, r.getValue(key)))
        
def reset_doses(r):
    """ Sets all doses to zero. """
    for key in doses_keys:
        r.setValue('init({})'.format(key), 0)  # [mg] 
        
from collections import namedtuple
Dosing = namedtuple('Dosing', ['substance', 'route', 'dose', 'unit'])

def set_dosing(r, dosing, show=False):
    """ Sets dosing for simulation. """
    if dosing.route == "oral":
        pid = "PODOSE_{}".format(dosing.substance)
    elif dosing.route == "iv":
        pid = "IVDOSE_{}".format(dosing.substance)
    else:
        raise ValueError("Invalid dosing route: {}".format(dosing.route))
        
    # get dose in [mg]
    dose = dosing.dose
    if dosing.unit.endswith("kg"):
        dose = dose * r.BW
    
    # reset the model
    r.reset()
    reset_doses(r)
    r.setValue('init({})'.format(pid), dose)  # set dose in [mg]
    r.reset(SelectionRecord.GLOBAL_PARAMETER)
    r.reset()
    # r.resetAll()?
    if show:
        print_doses(r)
    
def plot_results(s, name=None):
    # full timecourse
    f, ((ax1, ax2, ax3), (ax4, ax5, ax6)) = plt.subplots(2,3, figsize=(15,8))
    f.subplots_adjust(wspace=.3, hspace=0.3)
    axes = (ax1, ax2, ax3, ax4, ax5, ax6)
    for k, skey in enumerate(substances): 
        ax, title = axes[k], titles[k]
        time = s["time"]
        ax.plot(time, s['Cli_{}'.format(skey)], label='{} liver'.format(skey), color='black', linestyle="--")
        ax.plot(time, s['Cve_{}'.format(skey)], label='{} venous blood'.format(skey), color='blue', linewidth=2.0)
        ax.plot(time, s['Clu_{}'.format(skey)], label='{} lung'.format(skey), color='red', linewidth=2.0)
        
        if name is not None:
            title = "{} ({})".format(title, name)
        ax.set_title(title)
        ax.set_ylabel('concentration [mg/l]')
        ax.legend()
    
    for ax in (ax4, ax5, ax6):
        ax.set_xlabel('time [h]')
    plt.show()
    
# Molecular weights for conversion
Mr_apap = 151.16  # [g/mole] C8H9NO2 (CHEBI:46195)
Mr_apap_glu = 327.29  # [g/mole] C14H17NO8 (CHEBI:32636)
Mr_apap_sul = 231.23  # [g/mole] C8H9NO5S (CHEBI:32635)

# consistent plotting styles
kwargs_data = { 'marker': 's', 'linestyle': '--', 'linewidth': 1}
kwargs_sim = { 'marker': None, 'linestyle': '-', 'linewidth': 2}
colors = {'metc13': 'black', 'apap': 'black', 'apap_glu': 'darkblue', 'apap_sul': 'darkred', 'apap_cys': 'darkgreen', 'dob':'darkorange'}

Example Simulations¶

Oral or IV dosing of substances (C13-methacetin, paracetamol, bicarbonate). In the example oral and IV dosing of C13-methacetin.

In [3]:
from roadrunner import SelectionRecord
d1 = Dosing(substance="metc13", route="oral", dose=100.0, unit="mg")
set_dosing(r, d1)
s1 = r.simulate(start=0, end=8, steps=800)
plot_results(s1, name="metc13 oral 100 [mg]")

d2 = Dosing(substance="metc13", route="iv", dose=100.0, unit="mg")
set_dosing(r, d2)
s2 = r.simulate(start=0, end=8, steps=800)
plot_results(s2, name="metc13 iv 100 [mg]")

apap_dir = '/home/mkoenig/git/acetaminophen/literature/'
def load_apap_data(fid, sep="\t", show=True):
    """ Loads data from given figure/table id.
    Displays the first rows of the dataframe by default.
    """
    df = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(apap_dir, '{}.csv'.format(fid)), sep=sep, comment="#")
    if show == True:
        display(df.head())
        print(fid)
    return df

In [16]:
# data preprocessing
Nexp = 5  # number of different experiments performed
Nsubject = 28  # subjects in the study
generic_col_indices = range(13)  # generic columns at the beginning of the dataset

substance_prefixes = ['Meth', 'Parac', 'DOB']
data_ids = ["metc13", "apap", "dob"] 

times = {
    'DOB': [1, 2, 5, 10, 20, 30, 50, 60, 70], 
    'Meth': [0, 0.5, 1, 2, 5, 10, 20, 30, 60],
    'Parac': [0, 0.5, 1, 2, 5, 10, 20, 30, 60] 
}
datasets = []

# process all the experiments
for k in range(Nexp):
    dataset = {}
    for i, prefix in enumerate(substance_prefixes):
        data_id = data_ids[i]
        headers = []
        for t in times[prefix]:
            # handle special 0.5 column name
            if abs(t-0.5)<1E-6:
                t = '005'
            else:
                t = str('{:02d}'.format(t))
            header = '{}{:02d}_{}'.format(prefix, k+1, t)
            headers.append(header)
            
        # print(headers)
        data = hh2013[headers]
        da = data.transpose()
        # set time points as index
        da.index = times[prefix]
        dataset[data_id] = da

    datasets.append(dataset)

    # dataframe for given substance
    da = dataset[data_id]

    time = da.index

                label="mean+-std (n={})".format(len(da.columns)), **kwargs_data)
    ax.set_xlabel("time [min]")
    ax.set_ylabel(data_id)
    ax.set_title(title)

for ax in axes:
